# Changelog (maintainer)

**Canonical file:** [`docs/changelog.md`](../../docs/changelog.md)

## What belongs in the changelog

| Section | Include | Exclude |
|---------|---------|---------|
| **Breaking** | Removed CLI/API paths, renames, layout changes users must act on | Internal refactors, test-only changes |
| **Added** | New `[project.scripts]` CLI, new `Client.<Kind>` / public API, shipped agent skills with distinct playbooks | Maintainer scripts, CI-only wiring, routine model regen |
| **Changed** | Behavior or defaults that affect consumers without a hard break; optional release footnote when models align to a new OpenAPI snapshot | Doc-only edits unless user-visible |

### Added — detail

**Include when upgraders gain a new capability:**

- New console script or workflow CLI (`pyproject.toml` → `[project.scripts]`).
- New registry facade, operation, or public `endorlabs.*` helper consumers call.
- New shipped skill under `sdk/skills/` (one bullet per skill id, or one grouped bullet listing ids).
- New optional PyPI extra or contract behavior documented in `contracts.md`.

**Prefer one grouped bullet** when landing several skills in one release: “Agent skills: `endor-foo`, `endor-bar` (shipped `MANIFEST.json`).”

### Model sync / backend OpenAPI

| Situation | Changelog |
|-----------|-----------|
| Regen only; same resources and ops | **Omit** (or one **Changed** footnote at release: “Models aligned to platform OpenAPI snapshot.”) |
| New resources, ops, or create kwargs in generated reference | **Added** — name the resource or capability |
| Removed resource, stricter validation, facade break | **Breaking** |
| Payload tolerance / validation fixes callers saw | **Changed** |

Detail stays in [`docs/contributing/docs-drift-workflow.md`](../docs/contributing/docs-drift-workflow.md) and `docs/generated-reference/` — do not replay every regen PR.

### Skills / workflows

- **New skill** → **Added** (or grouped).
- **Skill playbook fix** → **Changed** only when behavior materially changes for agents/users.
- **Workflow module without new console script** → usually omit unless it is the main upgrade reason.

## PR intake (before merge)

Copy into the PR description ([`.github/pull_request_template.md`](../../.github/pull_request_template.md)). When **user-facing**, append the **Summary** line to **`docs/changelog.md` → Unreleased** in the same PR.

```markdown
- [ ] Not user-facing → no Unreleased edit
- [ ] User-facing → one bullet under Added | Changed | Breaking

Section: Added | Changed | Breaking | none
Summary: (one imperative sentence)
Audience: sdk-user | agent-skill | both
Migration: (Breaking only)
```

Optional structured fields: [`agent-knowledge/schema/changelog-intake.schema.json`](../schema/changelog-intake.schema.json) (reference only; not CI-gated).

**PR title hints (triage, not auto-changelog):** `feat(cli): …` · `fix(sdk): …` · `chore(model-sync): …` (usually no Unreleased line).

## Workflow

1. Stage under **`## Unreleased`** while work lands on `main`.
2. At release, rename **Unreleased** → **`## X.Y.Z`** (keep subsections Added / Changed / Breaking).
3. Leave a fresh empty **Unreleased** (subsection headers only until the next entry).
4. Link from product docs (e.g. [estate/README.md](../../docs/estate/README.md)) to **`docs/changelog.md`** — not duplicate migration files.

**Release cut checklist** (see also [release-publishing.md](../../docs/contributing/release-publishing.md)):

1. Collapse model-sync-only PRs into one **Changed** footnote or omit.
2. Promote **Unreleased** → `## X.Y.Z`; reset **Unreleased** headers.
3. Grep for removed CLI/API names; update durable docs to **current** behavior only.

Do **not** auto-generate `docs/changelog.md` from `git log`.

## Do not

- Add `docs/**/*-migration.md` or long breaking tables outside the changelog.
- Put session reports or readiness assessments in the changelog (use workspace `notes/`).
- Duplicate the same breaking table in skills, contributing guides, and changelog.

When you add a **Breaking** entry, grep for old names/paths and update durable docs ([`docs/estate/`](../../docs/estate/), skills) to describe **current** behavior only; point upgraders at the changelog.
